      <img alt="An example :class:`Gtk.Calendar`" src="calendar.png">
    </picture>

    A :class:`Gtk.Calendar` can be created with :meth:`Gtk.Calendar.new`.

    The selected date can be retrieved from a :class:`Gtk.Calendar` using
    :meth:`Gtk.Calendar.get_date`.
    It can be altered with :meth:`Gtk.Calendar.set_date`.

    To place a visual marker on a particular day, use
    :meth:`Gtk.Calendar.mark_day` and to remove the marker,
    :meth:`Gtk.Calendar.unmark_day`. Alternative, all
    marks can be cleared with :meth:`Gtk.Calendar.clear_marks`.

    Users should be aware that, although the Gregorian calendar is the
    legal calendar in most countries, it was adopted progressively
    between 1582 and 1929. Display before these dates is likely to be
    historically incorrect.

    # Shortcuts and Gestures

    :class:`Gtk.Calendar` supports the following gestures:

    - Scrolling up or down will switch to the previous or next month.
    - Date strings can be dropped for setting the current day.

