    :attr:`Gtk.ColumnView.show-column-separators` properties offer a simple way
    to display separators between the rows or columns.

    :class:`Gtk.ColumnView` allows the user to select items according to the selection
    characteristics of the model. For models that allow multiple selected items,
    it is possible to turn on *rubberband selection*, using
    :attr:`Gtk.ColumnView.enable-rubberband`.

    The column view supports sorting that can be customized by the user by
    clicking on column headers. To set this up, the :class:`Gtk.Sorter` returned by
    :meth:`Gtk.ColumnView.get_sorter` must be attached to a sort model for the
    data that the view is showing, and the columns must have sorters attached to
    them by calling :meth:`Gtk.ColumnViewColumn.set_sorter`. The initial sort
    order can be set with :meth:`Gtk.ColumnView.sort_by_column`.

    The column view also supports interactive resizing and reordering of
