    and you can get it with :meth:`Gtk.Widget.get_native`.

    To get the surface of a :class:`Gtk.Native`, use :meth:`Gtk.Native.get_surface`.
    It is also possible to find the :class:`Gtk.Native` to which a surface
    belongs, with :func:`Gtk.Native.get_for_surface`.

    In addition to a :class:`Gdk.Surface`, a :class:`Gtk.Native` also provides
    a :class:`Gsk.Renderer` for rendering on that surface. To get the
    renderer, use :meth:`Gtk.Native.get_renderer`.
