    Allows to enter or change numeric values.

    <picture>
      <source srcset="spinbutton-dark.png" media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)">
      <img alt="An example :class:`Gtk.SpinButton`" src="spinbutton.png">
    </picture>

    Rather than having to directly type a number into a :class:`Gtk.Entry`,
    :class:`Gtk.SpinButton` allows the user to click on one of two arrows
    to increment or decrement the displayed value. A value can still be
    typed in, with the bonus that it can be checked to ensure it is in a
    given range.

    The main properties of a :class:`Gtk.SpinButton` are through an adjustment.
    See the :class:`Gtk.Adjustment` documentation for more details about
    an adjustment's properties.

    Note that :class:`Gtk.SpinButton` will by default make its entry large enough
    to accommodate the lower and upper bounds of the adjustment. If this
    is not desired, the automatic sizing can be turned off by explicitly
    setting :attr:`Gtk.Editable.width-chars` to a value != -1.

    ## Using a :class:`Gtk.SpinButton` to get an integer

    .. code-block:: c

        // Provides a function to retrieve an integer value from a :class:`Gtk.SpinButton`
        // and creates a spin button to model percentage values.

        int
        grab_int_value (:class:`Gtk.SpinButton` *button,
                        gpointer       user_data)
        {
          return :meth:`Gtk.SpinButton.get_value_as_int` (button);
        }

        void
        create_integer_spin_button (void)
        {

          :class:`Gtk.Widget` *window, *button;
          :class:`Gtk.Adjustment` *adjustment;

          adjustment = :meth:`Gtk.Adjustment.new` (50.0, 0.0, 100.0, 1.0, 5.0, 0.0);

          window = :meth:`Gtk.Window.new`;

          // creates the spinbutton, with no decimal places
          button = :meth:`Gtk.SpinButton.new` (adjustment, 1.0, 0);
          :meth:`Gtk.Window.set_child` (GTK_WINDOW (window), button);

          :meth:`Gtk.Window.present` (GTK_WINDOW (window));
        }

    ## Using a :class:`Gtk.SpinButton` to get a floating point value

    .. code-block:: c

        // Provides a function to retrieve a floating point value from a
        // :class:`Gtk.SpinButton`, and creates a high precision spin button.

        float
        grab_float_value (:class:`Gtk.SpinButton` *button,
                          gpointer       user_data)
        {
          return :meth:`Gtk.SpinButton.get_value` (button);
        }

        void
        create_floating_spin_button (void)
        {
          :class:`Gtk.Widget` *window, *button;
          :class:`Gtk.Adjustment` *adjustment;

          adjustment = :meth:`Gtk.Adjustment.new` (2.500, 0.0, 5.0, 0.001, 0.1, 0.0);

          window = :meth:`Gtk.Window.new`;

          // creates the spinbutton, with three decimal places
          button = :meth:`Gtk.SpinButton.new` (adjustment, 0.001, 3);
          :meth:`Gtk.Window.set_child` (GTK_WINDOW (window), button);

          :meth:`Gtk.Window.present` (GTK_WINDOW (window));
        }

    # Shortcuts and Gestures

    The following signals have default keybindings:

    - ``Gtk.SpinButton::change-value``

    # CSS nodes

    .. code-block:: text

        spinbutton.horizontal
        ├── text
        │    ├── undershoot.left
        │    ╰── undershoot.right
        ├── button.down
        ╰── button.up

    .. code-block:: text

        spinbutton.vertical
        ├── button.up
        ├── text
        │    ├── undershoot.left
        │    ╰── undershoot.right
        ╰── button.down

    :class:`Gtk.SpinButton`s main CSS node has the name spinbutton. It creates subnodes
    for the entry and the two buttons, with these names. The button nodes have
    the style classes .up and .down. The :class:`Gtk.Text` subnodes (if present) are put
    below the text node. The orientation of the spin button is reflected in
    the .vertical or .horizontal style class on the main node.

    # Accessibility

    :class:`Gtk.SpinButton` uses the :class:`Gtk.AccessibleRole.spin_button` role.
    """
    gimeta: ClassVar[_GIMeta]
    activates_default: bool
    adjustment: Adjustment
    climb_rate: float
    digits: int
    numeric: bool
    snap_to_ticks: bool
    update_policy: SpinButtonUpdatePolicy | int
    value: float
    wrap: bool
    def __init__(self, *, activates_default: bool = ..., adjustment: Adjustment = ..., climb_rate: float = ..., digits: int = ..., numeric: bool = ..., snap_to_ticks: bool = ..., update_policy: SpinButtonUpdatePolicy | int = ..., value: float = ..., wrap: bool = ..., **kwargs: Any) -> None: ...
    @classmethod
    def new(cls, *args: Any, **kwargs: Any) -> Self: ...
    @classmethod
    def new_with_range(cls, min: float, max: float, step: float) -> Self:
        """
        Creates a new :class:`Gtk.SpinButton` with the given properties.

        This is a convenience constructor that allows creation
        of a numeric :class:`Gtk.SpinButton` without manually creating
        an adjustment. The value is initially set to the minimum
        value and a page increment of 10 * ``step`` is the default.
        The precision of the spin button is equivalent to the
        precision of ``step``.

        Note that the way in which the precision is derived works
        best if ``step`` is a power of ten. If the resulting precision
        is not suitable for your needs, use
        :meth:`Gtk.SpinButton.set_digits` to correct it.
        """
    def configure(self, adjustment: Adjustment | None, climb_rate: float, digits: int) -> None:
        """
        Changes the properties of an existing spin button.

        The adjustment, climb rate, and number of decimal places
        are updated accordingly.
        """
    def get_activates_default(self) -> bool:
        """
        Retrieves the value set by :meth:`Gtk.SpinButton.set_activates_default`.
        """
    def get_adjustment(self) -> Adjustment:
        """
        Get the adjustment associated with a :class:`Gtk.SpinButton`.
        """
    def get_climb_rate(self) -> float:
        """
        Returns the acceleration rate for repeated changes.
        """
    def get_digits(self) -> int:
        """
        Fetches the precision of ``spin_button``.
        """
    def get_increments(self) -> tuple[float, float]:
        """
        Gets the current step and page the increments
        used by ``spin_button``.

        See :meth:`Gtk.SpinButton.set_increments`.
        """
    def get_numeric(self) -> bool:
        """
        Returns whether non-numeric text can be typed into the spin button.
        """
    def get_range(self) -> tuple[float, float]:
        """
        Gets the range allowed for ``spin_button``.

        See :meth:`Gtk.SpinButton.set_range`.
        """
    def get_snap_to_ticks(self) -> bool:
        """
        Returns whether the values are corrected to the nearest step.
        """
    def get_update_policy(self) -> SpinButtonUpdatePolicy:
        """
        Gets the update behavior of a spin button.

        See :meth:`Gtk.SpinButton.set_update_policy`.
        """
    def get_value(self) -> float:
        """
        Get the value in the ``spin_button``.
        """
    def get_value_as_int(self) -> int:
        """
        Get the value ``spin_button`` represented as an integer.
        """
    def get_wrap(self) -> bool:
        """
        Returns whether the spin button’s value wraps around to the
        opposite limit when the upper or lower limit of the range is
        exceeded.
        """
    def set_activates_default(self, activates_default: bool) -> None:
        """
        Sets whether activating the spin button will activate the default
        widget for the window containing the spin button.

        See ``Gtk.SpinButton::activate`` for what counts as activation.
        """
    def set_adjustment(self, adjustment: Adjustment) -> None:
        """
        Replaces the :class:`Gtk.Adjustment` associated with ``spin_button``.
        """
    def set_climb_rate(self, climb_rate: float) -> None:
        """
        Sets the acceleration rate for repeated changes when you
        hold down a button or key.
        """
    def set_digits(self, digits: int) -> None:
        """
        Set the precision to be displayed by ``spin_button``.

        Up to 20 digit precision is allowed.
        """
    def set_increments(self, step: float, page: float) -> None:
        """
        Sets the step and page increments for spin_button.

        This affects how quickly the value changes when
        the spin button’s arrows are activated.
        """
    def set_numeric(self, numeric: bool) -> None:
        """
        Sets the flag that determines if non-numeric text can be typed
